layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Racial Terror — Lynching as Political Weapon
description: Between 1877 and 1950, more than 4,000 Black Americans were lynched in the South. This was not random violence. It was a systematic political tool used to destroy Black political power, enforce economic subordination, and terrorize communities into submission.
permalink: /lynching/
---

<section class="hero hero--short" id="chapter-intro" data-chapter="Lynching">
  <div class="hero__content">
